"Font availability depends on the board firmware build and the UI API you "
"use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:59 1fbe71c20e734b6996627fca82fcbc67
msgid "**LVGL / m5ui widget fonts**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:61 bb4f70ade78849899c8d5ff28e7f7d46
msgid ""
"For ``m5ui`` widgets, use LVGL font objects such as "
"``lv.font_montserrat_*``. Most M5Stack firmware builds include these "
"Montserrat fonts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:64 2c7212e77a36446f93438f3452338e41
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_12`` - Extra small text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:65 f048e35f303d4a9f9c0fb26e84b07254
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_14`` - Default font"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:66 f048e35f303d4a9f9c0fb26e84b07254
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_16`` - Medium text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:67 f048e35f303d4a9f9c0fb26e84b07254
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_18`` - Medium-large text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:68 3b1eb71d451b429681cb3391c2dfb933
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_24`` - Large text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:69 3b1eb71d451b429681cb3391c2dfb933
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_40`` - Extra-large text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:70 3b1eb71d451b429681cb3391c2dfb933
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_44`` - Extra-large text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:71 3b1eb71d451b429681cb3391c2dfb933
msgid "``lv.font_montserrat_48`` - Extra-large text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:73 5a4d320e9157434cbac0e20652ceb58f
msgid ""
"Some builds, such as Tab5, also include ``lv.font_montserrat_20``, "
"``lv.font_montserrat_22``, ``lv.font_montserrat_30``, and "
"``lv.font_montserrat_36``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:77 a4d0fd1aeb1741bbad4a73cdd7475e3e
msgid "**M5.Lcd / Widgets CJK fonts**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:79 a1b279159c7148ed8e66ec76beadc661
msgid ""
"For drawing text with ``M5.Lcd`` or widgets based on ``M5.Widgets``, use "
"``M5.Lcd.FONTS``. Most firmware builds also include these 24 px CJK "
"fonts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:82 a455d0b73aff4f15abbb0b2f28cbf27a
msgid "``M5.Lcd.FONTS.AlibabaPuHuiTiCN24`` - Simplified Chinese"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:83 7092f0cd501b41a1a4a508906c55e5ef
msgid "``M5.Lcd.FONTS.AlibabaSansJA24`` - Japanese"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:84 b21a60555e5f44d08ccba3694b2ab50d
msgid "``M5.Lcd.FONTS.AlibabaSansKR24`` - Korean"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:86 d2df9a6c5ef8419ea1ca495a547b8033
msgid ""
"The older ``EFontCN24``, ``EFontJA24``, and ``EFontKR24`` names are "
"deprecated aliases; prefer the ``Alibaba*`` names above. These CJK fonts "
"may be disabled on small-flash or resource-constrained firmware builds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:92 e4ab5525b2d1499fa807e323ad73b416
msgid ""
"Do not assume every font is available on every device. If your code may "
"run on multiple boards, use common fonts or check availability before "
"using an optional size/font, for example ``hasattr(lv, "
"\"font_montserrat_20\")`` for LVGL fonts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/m5ui/index.rst:97 171bfbfa6a684127bd13c5a67ba6d5b3
